How to Recognize a Lie
A glimpse of recent headlines suggests how serious and ubiquitous lies and deception are in everyday life.
Republican presidential candidate Herman Cain has his hands full with the accusation that he sexually harassed several women - both sides claim that the other one is lying.
Administrators at Penn State University were accused of perjury while trying to hide records of a retired football coach sexually assaulting a boy.
