Climate Disaster Slowed the Economy
During the first year of the reign of Maria López Valdez, unemployment and unreliability increased in Sinaloa, foreign investment decreased and the economy with them
This is the first year of the reign of Maria López Valdez, which is called the government of change itself. This government has brought with it great expectations in terms of economic progress, but due to adverse weather conditions at the beginning of the year no growth was recorded and even the main indicators of economic development were reduced.
Low February temperatures have caused millions of losses in agriculture, reduced the possibilities for growth of the state economy, resulting in a reduction in economic activity by 3.6% in the first semester of this year.
According to the report on the damage caused by the Mexican Council for Sustainable Rural Development, the damage was recorded at 582 835 hectares of cultivated land, 78.03% of which was completely destroyed and some damage was found at the remaining 21.07%. Main destroyed crops include vegetables, maize and peas.
According to the National Institute for Statistics and Geography, the unemployment rate in the state increased during the first three quarters. From January to March, 55,053 residents of Sinaloa were unemployed, representing a unemployment rate of 4.53% of the economically active population. In the second quarter, unemployment increased to 5.28% and between July and August, the average unemployment rate continued to rise and reached 6.19%, representing approximately 74,000 unemployed people.
Less liquidity
According to Gerard López Cervantes, Director of the Faculty of Economic and Social Sciences of the UAS, the increase in unemployment can be explained indirectly, based on actions taken at the level of public policy.
"We are witnessing rising unemployment, which is linked to various factors, including the loss of liquidity in the market due to the reduction of resources due to legislation approved by Congress in connection with the fight against money laundering. It is not easy for people who illegally seize dollars to earn, invest or use it for anything," he emphasized.
Stopping Migration
López Cervantes said that a demographic factor is also involved in the rise in unemployment.
"The number of people who go abroad to work in the United States has decreased, both because of difficult entry and then because even if these people get across borders, it is difficult for them to get a job. People remain and demand work from our state and thus unemployment is rising", he said.
Unreliability
According to the National Institute for Statistics and Democracy, 60.38% of the state’s employed people work without receiving social security benefits.
Other features of the labour market, such as low salaries, are added to unemployment and unreliable. In this administrative territory, the lowest salaries are from all over the country, as reported by the registers of the Mexican Institute of Social Security and the Labour Secretariat and Social Planning.
The average monthly income of workers in the state of Sinaloa until September was 5,352 pesetas, well below the national average, which ranges from 7,375 pesetas.
Shortening of foreign direct investment
Along with the decline in economic activity and the increase in unemployment, the most significant decline in foreign direct investment in 2011 has also been recorded in the last 10 years. According to the Ministry of Finance, foreign direct investment reached $630,697 between January and June, representing a decrease of 87.74% compared to $5,14,312 for the same period in the previous year.
On the other hand, the Ministry for Economic Development of the Government of the State lists investments of 17 280 million pesetas per year.
Debt
In the context of the economic downturn scenario, the state government asked the state congress in July to approve a 3 billion peso loan, which would be intended to invest in infrastructure projects in 18 urban areas to revive the economy. The local congress approved a 2 600 million peso loan. No debt gains were recorded until November, in any sector of the state economy.
Reactions
According to representatives of the business sector, the first year of the government of Mario López Valdés pointed to a lack of government management capabilities.
Miguel Loredo López, Chairman of the National Chamber of Transformation Industry, said that in 2011, the will of individual sectors, including the government itself, was missing.
"The development of the economy in Sinaloa was really small during this year. We need to work intensively to get back the land we lost this year. In 2012 we have to double our efforts, we have lacked harmonisation of the efforts of all of us and, in particular, the correct and synchronised functioning of this new government. Hopefully, next year will be much better," he said.
Slowness of the economy
Loredo López said that events like frosts at the beginning of the year stopped the state economy and reduced its development and growth.
"Weak economic movement was caused by a number of events, including frosts. One of the main consequences was the slowdown of the economy, which did not recover quickly enough to restore dynamism, which would enable it to achieve an acceptable level of movement of processes, products and services. That is why we found ourselves well below the expected forecasts at the end of the year", he said.
Redefined mission
According to Teodor Salazar Uriart, President of the Confederation of the Mexican Republic in Sinaloa, the state needs to be pushed into more dynamic productive activities.
"In general, we observe that it is working. We believe that a long-term plan should be prepared in which the goals and economic direction of the state would be redefined, because it is important that all the potential material and human resources that Sinaloa has be mobilised", he said.
The Work That Is Before Us
Chairman Coparmex stressed the importance of establishing a vision of the future that would better manage the government's efforts.
"In general, I would say that the government has tried to achieve good results in various areas, some progress has been made in the area of economic development, but it is important to establish a long-term plan", he said.
He said that the current administration has shown progress with regard to the conduct of public policy.
"There are elements that make it possible to say that the government is trying to be friendly. I can say that there is work done here and I believe that the government is aware that there is also a lot of work ahead of us," he said.
