"I do not think that even if she did, it would affect the autonomy of the regulatory authority", recalling that planning public policies in strategic areas such as the telecommunications sector is the responsibility of a federal executive, who has a constitutional mandate to determine the direction of the state.
Replacing analogous signals by digital is one of the biggest changes the world has seen in recent years. It is related to better use of radio spectrum, better signal quality and more channels.
It believes that delaying change would mean delaying the benefits of digitisation, which requires decisions on public interest, because digitisation has not only a technical dimension, but "it also affects economic, social, political and national security issues".
