In this way, a partial census of votes, one or more electoral packages, will be possible under the following conditions: election results do not agree; there is no record of the census and calculation in the appropriate box or the chairman does not have it; or if errors and obvious violations of electoral results have occurred.
In addition, the total recalculation of votes in all ballots will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between the potential winner of the election and the candidate in the second place is less than or equal to one percentage point; whenever an express request by the party representative and/or the coalition proposed by the candidate in the second place appears at the beginning of the session.
The total count of votes will also be possible if, after a proper count, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point and also if there is an express request from the political party whose candidate ended in second place. In that case, the electoral packages for which a partial census was made will be eliminated.
