Who influences you as a bass player?
Lots of people.
I'm the first to think of Geezer Butler, John Entwistle, C.J. Ramone, John Doe, Paul McCartney, Chuck Dukowski...
There are so many that I could talk about bass players I like all night.
How did Pearl Jam manage to hold the grunge even though it's no longer in fashion?
I think we've all always felt apart from the word grunge.
When it comes to grunge, I think of groups that I mentioned as Mudhoney, Soundgarden, Nirvana and all the others that were created at the same time. And if music is so valid today, it's something great, because it's music that's worth listening to, and bands like Mudhoney are playing better music today than ever.
In the beginning, your music had a slightly bleak character and is now more positive.
