Fujimori was hospitalized again for medical tests
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized in a public hospital on Tuesday, where he will be tested for muscle loss in the lower extremities, informed by his attending physician.
The 72 - year - old Fujimori, who is serving 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed by his government (1990 - 2000), suffers from several diseases, including tongue cancer, which has been operated on four times and are currently under medical control.
A Member of Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal physician, told TV station Canal N that Fujimori will be undergoing tests within three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases, where they should find out why he is in pain and why he is losing strength in his lower limbs.
Aguinaga said that, in his opinion, Fujimori might be pardoned for humanitarian reasons, but the former president himself does not want mercy because he feels innocent.
He was operated on four times because of tongue cancer, lost 18 kilograms, and other disorders such as severe erosive gastritis, pancreatic cyst, kidney stones, high blood pressure and circulatory problems in the legs were added to these problems, and the doctor named them.
Fujimori has served his sentence since September 2007 at the National Directorate of Special Police Operations.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the death of 25 persons who killed the murderous squadron of troops operating illegally in the first years of his reign.
