On Tuesday, President Álvaro Colom announced that he had taken action on the issue of the extradition of former President Alfons Portillo, to be held accountable in the United States for a conspiracy to launder $70 million.
This is the end of the process for Guatemala to respond at the request of the northern country requesting Portilla’s extradition to be judged.
