In addition to Portilla, Sergio Ruano Marroquín will be released for murder and grievous bodily harm and Edgar Estrada Morales and Víctor Estrada Paredes, both for drug trafficking.
Colom's move means a step in execution after all the judicial and constitutional instances were exhausted to lead the trial against the former president who ruled between 2000 and 2004.
