But fingerprints don't lie.
Along with the galton magnifying glass, the ink and the transplanter and the light, Eliaszar began to compare the dactyl records of the corpse to the card entries.
The eye did not disappoint him: it was Alfonso Cano.
That same night, a man from Puerto Tejada was commissioned to confirm to the Secretary of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinzón, whether he really was the supreme commander of Farc.
Track Search
